SOURCE ATTRIBUTION
------------------

This database was produced by the bsos extraction pipeline. The pipeline read
technical documents to discover building concepts and infer factual relationships
between them. The assertions stored in bsos.db are LLM-generated factual claims
expressed in the tool's own language; they are not reproductions of source text.

Sources used during extraction:

1. A Pattern Language: Towns, Buildings, Construction
   Christopher Alexander, Sara Ishikawa, Murray Silverstein
   Oxford University Press, 1977. ISBN 978-0-19-501919-3.

   The pattern names, numbers, identifiers, confidence ratings, and higher/lower
   pattern graph stored in bsos.db are factual and structural data. The problem
   and solution prose in the patterns table was generated by this tool's own
   pipeline (not reproduced from the book).

2. IFC 2x Edition 3 — Model Implementation Guide, Version 2.0 (May 2009)
   Thomas Liebich / buildingSMART International Modeling Support Group
   Copyright © 1996–2009 buildingSMART International. All rights reserved.

   This document is published as "All rights reserved" with no redistribution
   licence. The assertions derived from it describe factual technical relationships
   defined by the IFC standard (entity names, property sets, containment rules).
   Facts and technical standards are not copyrightable expression; only the
   creative expression of the source document is protected. No text from this
   document appears in bsos.db. If you have concerns about redistribution in
   your jurisdiction, consult a legal adviser.

3. IFC : concepts, principes et applications pratiques
   Innovation Paper n° 51 (July 2025)
   S. Boeykens, M. De Prins, D. Froyen / Buildwise (Cluster Digital Construction)
   Copyright © 2025 Buildwise. Reproduction requires written consent of the editor.

   As with source 2 above, the assertions derived from this document describe
   factual IFC technical relationships. No text from this document appears in
   bsos.db.


